Sentencas: The initialization of an anode-supported single-chamber solid-oxide fuel cell, with NiO+SM0.2Ce0.8O1.9 anode and Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta+Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 cathode, was investigated.
Titulo: Initialization of a methane-fueled single-chamber solid-oxide fuel cell with NiO plus SDC anode and BSCF plus SDC cathode

Sentencas: The initialization process had significant impact on the observed performance of the fuel cell.
Titulo: Initialization of a methane-fueled single-chamber solid-oxide fuel cell with NiO plus SDC anode and BSCF plus SDC cathode

Sentencas: The in situ reduction of the anode by a methane-air mixture failed.
Titulo: Initialization of a methane-fueled single-chamber solid-oxide fuel cell with NiO plus SDC anode and BSCF plus SDC cathode

Sentencas: Although pure methane did reduce the nickel oxide, it also resulted in severe carbon coking over the anode and serious distortion of the fuel cell.
Titulo: Initialization of a methane-fueled single-chamber solid-oxide fuel cell with NiO plus SDC anode and BSCF plus SDC cathode

Sentencas: In situ initialization by hydrogen led to simultaneous reduction of both the anode and cathode; however, the cell still delivered a maximum power density of similar to 350 mW cm(-2), attributed to the re-formation of the BSCF phase under the methane-air atmosphere at high temperatures.
Titulo: Initialization of a methane-fueled single-chamber solid-oxide fuel cell with NiO plus SDC anode and BSCF plus SDC cathode

Sentencas: The ex situ reduction method appeared to be the most promising.
Titulo: Initialization of a methane-fueled single-chamber solid-oxide fuel cell with NiO plus SDC anode and BSCF plus SDC cathode

Sentencas: The activated fuel cell showed a peak power density of similar to 570 mW cm(-2) at a furnace temperature of 600 degrees C, with the main polarization resistance contributed from the electrolyte.
Titulo: Initialization of a methane-fueled single-chamber solid-oxide fuel cell with NiO plus SDC anode and BSCF plus SDC cathode
